  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Just wanted to drop this here in case you guys were interested in what Preact did before switching to the Promise method:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/developit/preact/commit/6954d7549f35b5c32421c6855ee29ffda01137d1\r\n\r\n```js\r\nlet ch;\r\ntry { ch = new MessageChannel(); } catch (e) {}\r\nexport const defer = ch ? ( f => {\r\n  ch.port1.onmessage = f;\r\n  ch.port2.postMessage('');\r\n}) : setTimeout;\r\n```\r\n\r\nAFAIK this had worse browser support than Promise, the runtime performance was slightly worse, and it swallowed errors.  Promise falling back to setTimeout is a great option.",
    "created_at": "2017-01-06T16:48:49Z",
